{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"a3c48892ed18baec","x":-109,"y":776,"width":250,"height":60,"type":"text","text":""},
		{"id":"title","type":"text","text":"# Study Content Overview — For Teacher Review\n*What is taught, in what order, at what difficulty · 24 lessons · 96 items · 80 grammar points*","x":-200,"y":-1250,"width":800,"height":80},
		{"id":"unit1","type":"text","text":"## Unit 1 — Basics\n*First words and survival phrases*\n\n### Lesson 001: Hello & Goodbye\n| Vietnamese | English | Type |\n|---|---|---|\n| xin chào | hello (polite) | word |\n| tạm biệt | goodbye | word |\n| cảm ơn | thank you | word |\n| không | no / not | word |\n| bạn | you (friend) | word |\n\n### Lesson 002: My Name Is…\n| Vietnamese | English | Type |\n|---|---|---|\n| Bạn tên là gì? | What is your name? | sentence |\n| tôi tên là {NAME} | my name is… | phrase |\n| Rất vui được gặp bạn. | Nice to meet you. | sentence |\n\n### Lesson 003: Please & Sorry\n| Vietnamese | English | Type |\n|---|---|---|\n| xin lỗi | sorry / excuse me | word |\n| làm ơn | please | word |\n| Tôi không hiểu. | I don't understand. | sentence |\n| Bạn có thể nói chậm lại không? | Can you speak more slowly? | sentence |\n\n### Lesson 004: Numbers 1–10\n| Vietnamese | English |\n|---|---|\n| một, hai, ba, bốn, năm | 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 |\n| sáu, bảy, tám, chín, mười | 6, 7, 8, 9, 10 |\n\n### Lesson 005: I Want…\n| Vietnamese | English | Type |\n|---|---|---|\n| cà phê | coffee | word |\n| trà | tea | word |\n| nước | water | word |\n| muốn | to want | word |\n| Cho tôi một cà phê, làm ơn. | Give me a coffee, please. | sentence |\n| Tôi muốn một trà. | I want a tea. | sentence |\n\n**Skills:** ⚡ Vowels Practice · 📗 Tone Marks Practice\n**Items:** 27 words/phrases/sentences\n**🏆 Unit Test:** 12 questions from all 5 lessons","x":-1350,"y":-1120,"width":470,"height":1060,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"unit2","type":"text","text":"## Unit 2 — Coffee Culture\n*Ordering food and asking prices*\n\n### Lesson 006: Café Ordering\n| Vietnamese | English | Type |\n|---|---|---|\n| cà phê sữa đá | iced milk coffee | word |\n| sữa | milk | word |\n| đá | ice | word |\n| nóng | hot | word |\n| Cho tôi một cà phê sữa đá. | Give me an iced milk coffee. | sentence |\n\n### Lesson 007: Vietnamese Food\n| Vietnamese | English | Type |\n|---|---|---|\n| phở | pho (noodle soup) | word |\n| bánh mì | Vietnamese sandwich | word |\n| bún | rice noodles | word |\n| cơm | rice | word |\n| bát | bowl | word |\n| ngon | delicious | word |\n| Tôi muốn một bát phở. | I want a bowl of pho. | sentence |\n\n### Lesson 008: How Much?\n| Vietnamese | English | Type |\n|---|---|---|\n| bao nhiêu | how much / how many | word |\n| tiền | money | word |\n| cái này | this (thing) | word |\n| đắt | expensive | word |\n| rẻ | cheap | word |\n| Cái này bao nhiêu tiền? | How much does this cost? | sentence |\n\n**Skills:** ⚡ Tone Mastery · 📗 Grammar: Subject + là\n**Items:** 18 words/phrases/sentences\n**🏆 Unit Test:** 12 questions from all 3 lessons","x":-830,"y":-1120,"width":470,"height":1060,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"unit3","type":"text","text":"## Unit 3 — Market Life\n*Shopping, colors, haggling, numbers*\n\n### Lesson 009: Colors & Descriptions\n| Vietnamese | English |\n|---|---|\n| màu | color |\n| đỏ, xanh, trắng, đen, vàng | red, blue/green, white, black, yellow |\n| to, nhỏ | big, small |\n| đẹp, xấu | beautiful, ugly |\n⚠️ `xanh` = both blue AND green (ambiguous)\n\n### Lesson 010: Haggling\n| Vietnamese | English | Dialect |\n|---|---|---|\n| mua, bán | buy, sell | both |\n| mắc | expensive | 🔴 Southern |\n| bớt, giảm | reduce / discount | both |\n| được không | is that OK? | both |\n| Mắc quá! Bớt đi. | Too expensive! Lower it. | 🔴 Southern |\n| Tôi muốn mua cái này. | I want to buy this. | both |\n\n### Lesson 011: Fruits & Vegetables\n| Vietnamese | English |\n|---|---|\n| trái cây | fruit |\n| cam, xoài, dừa, dưa hấu | orange, mango, coconut, watermelon |\n| rau, cà chua, khoai | vegetable, tomato, potato |\n\n### Lesson 012: Big Numbers\n| Vietnamese | English | Dialect |\n|---|---|---|\n| trăm | hundred | both |\n| nghìn | thousand | 🔵 Northern |\n| ngàn | thousand | 🔴 Southern |\n| triệu | million | both |\n| hóa đơn | bill / receipt | both |\n| Tính tiền, làm ơn. | The bill, please. | both |\n\n**Skills:** ⚡ Numbers Master · 📗 Grammar: Asking Questions\n**Items:** 26 words/phrases/sentences\n**🏆 Unit Test:** 12 questions from all 4 lessons","x":-310,"y":-1120,"width":470,"height":1060,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"unit4","type":"text","text":"## Unit 4 — Getting Around\n*Directions, transport, hotel, emergencies*\n\n### Lesson 013: Directions\n| Vietnamese | English | Dialect |\n|---|---|---|\n| đi | to go | both |\n| đường | road / street | both |\n| bên trái, bên phải | left, right | both |\n| thẳng | straight | both |\n| gần, xa | near, far | both |\n| Đi thẳng rồi quẹo trái. | Go straight then turn left. | 🔴 South |\n⚠️ `quẹo` is Southern; Northern = `rẽ`\n\n### Lesson 014: Taxi & Grab\n| Vietnamese | English |\n|---|---|\n| xe | vehicle |\n| xe ôm | motorbike taxi |\n| dừng lại | stop |\n| ở đây | here |\n| đến | to arrive / to |\n| Cho tôi đến khách sạn. | Take me to the hotel. |\n| Dừng ở đây, làm ơn. | Stop here, please. |\n\n### Lesson 015: At the Hotel\n| Vietnamese | English |\n|---|---|\n| khách sạn | hotel |\n| phòng | room |\n| chìa khóa | key |\n| giường | bed |\n| nhà vệ sinh | bathroom / toilet |\n| Phòng có wifi không? | Does the room have wifi? |\n\n### Lesson 016: Asking for Help\n| Vietnamese | English |\n|---|---|\n| giúp | to help |\n| tìm | to find / look for |\n| bị lạc | to be lost |\n| cần | to need |\n| gọi | to call |\n| Giúp tôi với! | Help me! |\n| Tôi bị lạc. | I am lost. |\n\n**Skills:** ⚡ TELEX Typing · 📗 Grammar: Giving Directions\n**Items:** 25 words/phrases/sentences\n**🏆 Unit Test:** 12 questions from all 4 lessons","x":210,"y":-1120,"width":470,"height":1060,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"unit5","type":"text","text":"## Unit 5 — Daily Life\n*Time, weather, family, home*\n\n### Lesson 017: Time & Schedule\n| Vietnamese | English |\n|---|---|\n| giờ, phút | hour, minute |\n| sáng, chiều, tối | morning, afternoon, evening |\n| hôm nay, ngày mai, hôm qua | today, tomorrow, yesterday |\n| Bây giờ là mấy giờ? | What time is it? |\n\n### Lesson 018: Weather & Seasons\n| Vietnamese | English |\n|---|---|\n| trời | sky / weather |\n| mưa, nắng, gió | rain, sunny, wind |\n| lạnh, mát | cold, cool |\n| Hôm nay trời đẹp quá! | The weather is so nice today! |\n\n### Lesson 019: Family\n| Vietnamese | English | Dialect |\n|---|---|---|\n| bố | father | 🔵 Northern |\n| ba | father | 🔴 Southern |\n| mẹ | mother | 🔵 Northern |\n| má | mother | 🔴 Southern |\n| anh, chị, em | older brother, older sister, younger sibling | both |\n| con | child | both |\n| vợ, chồng | wife, husband | both |\n⚠️ `ba` = also \"three\" (lesson 004) — potential confusion\n\n### Lesson 020: Around the House\n| Vietnamese | English |\n|---|---|\n| nhà | house / home |\n| nhà bếp | kitchen |\n| phòng ngủ, phòng khách | bedroom, living room |\n| cửa | door |\n| ghế, bàn | chair, table |\n\n**Skills:** ⚡ Pronouns & Kinship · 📗 Grammar: Time Expressions\n**Items:** 27 words/phrases/sentences\n**🏆 Unit Test:** 12 questions from all 4 lessons","x":730,"y":-1120,"width":470,"height":1060,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"unit6","type":"text","text":"## Unit 6 — Making Friends\n*Hobbies, feelings, socializing*\n\n### Lesson 021: Hobbies & Interests\n| Vietnamese | English |\n|---|---|\n| thích | to like / enjoy |\n| đi chơi | to hang out |\n| xem phim | to watch movies |\n| nghe nhạc | to listen to music |\n| nấu ăn, đọc sách | to cook, to read books |\n| Bạn thích làm gì? | What do you like to do? |\n\n### Lesson 022: Feelings & Opinions\n| Vietnamese | English |\n|---|---|\n| vui, buồn | happy, sad |\n| mệt | tired |\n| đói, khát | hungry, thirsty |\n| sợ | scared |\n| Tôi mệt quá. | I am so tired. |\n\n### Lesson 023: Invitations\n| Vietnamese | English |\n|---|---|\n| cuối tuần | weekend |\n| rảnh, bận | free, busy |\n| cùng | together |\n| hẹn | to make an appointment |\n| Cuối tuần bạn rảnh không? | Are you free this weekend? |\n| Đi chơi cùng tôi không? | Want to hang out with me? |\n\n### Lesson 024: At the Party\n| Vietnamese | English |\n|---|---|\n| chúc mừng | congratulations |\n| sinh nhật | birthday |\n| quà | gift / present |\n| tiệc | party / feast |\n| chụp hình | to take a photo |\n| Chúc mừng sinh nhật! | Happy birthday! |\n| Vui quá! | So fun! |\n\n**Skills:** ⚡ Flashcard Review · 📗 Grammar: Invitations\n**Items:** 25 words/phrases/sentences\n**🏆 Unit Test (Final):** 12 questions from all 4 lessons","x":1250,"y":-1120,"width":470,"height":1060,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"difficulty","type":"text","text":"## How Difficulty Progresses\n\n**Each lesson is studied 4 times (sessions) with increasing difficulty:**\n\n### Session 0 — Introduction (easiest)\nMostly recognition: match pairs, picture choice, multiple choice\nNo speaking exercises · Student just recognizes words\n\n### Session 1 — Reinforcement\nBalanced mix: less matching, some typing, first speaking exercise\nStudent starts producing answers\n\n### Session 2 — Production\nNo more matching · More word bank, reorder, fill-in-blank\nStudent builds sentences from parts\n\n### Session 3 — Mastery (hardest)\nNo pictures · Maximum speaking, typing, sentence building\nStudent produces language independently\n\n---\n\n**Exercise type counts per session:**\n\n| Exercise | S0 | S1 | S2 | S3 |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Match pairs | ✓ | ✓ | — | — |\n| Picture choice | 3 | 2 | 1 | 0 |\n| MCQ Vi→En | 4 | 2 | 2 | 1 |\n| Listen & choose | 2 | 2 | 1 | 1 |\n| MCQ En→Vi | 3 | 3 | 2 | 1 |\n| Listen & type | 1 | 2 | 2 | 2 |\n| Word bank | 1 | 1 | 2 | 2 |\n| Reorder words | 1 | 1 | 2 | 2 |\n| Fill blank | 1 | 1 | 2 | 2 |\n| Speak sentence | 0 | 1 | 1 | 2 |\n| **Total** | **~16** | **~16** | **~16** | **~16** |\n\n**After 4 sessions → lesson node complete → next node unlocks**","x":-1350,"y":10,"width":470,"height":1310,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"exercise_types","type":"text","text":"## Exercise Types Explained\n\n**1. Match Pairs**\nTwo columns: Vietnamese ↔ English. Tap to connect.\nGood for: initial word association\n\n**2. Picture Choice**\nShow image → pick correct Vietnamese from 4 options\nGood for: visual memory\n\n**3. MCQ: Vietnamese → English**\nSee Vietnamese word → pick English (3 choices)\nGood for: reading comprehension\n\n**4. Listen & Choose**\nHear audio → pick correct Vietnamese text (3 choices)\nGood for: listening comprehension\n\n**5. MCQ: English → Vietnamese**\nSee English → pick Vietnamese (3 choices)\nGood for: recall in target language\n\n**6. Listen & Type**\nHear audio → type the Vietnamese text\n*Accepts answers without diacritics (shows correct form)*\nGood for: listening + spelling\n\n**7. Word Bank (Sentence Building)**\nSee English sentence → tap Vietnamese word tokens in order\nGood for: word order practice\n\n**8. Reorder Words**\nScrambled Vietnamese sentence → drag into correct order\nGood for: syntax awareness\n\n**9. Fill in the Blank**\nVietnamese sentence with ____ → pick missing word\nGood for: contextual vocabulary\n\n**10. Speak Sentence**\nSee Vietnamese sentence → record pronunciation\nGood for: production + pronunciation","x":-830,"y":10,"width":470,"height":1150,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"grammar_roadmap","type":"text","text":"## Grammar in the Roadmap\n\nOnly 6 grammar points are embedded in the study path:\n\n| Unit | Grammar Skill Node | Topic |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Tone Marks Practice | (practice, not grammar) |\n| 2 | A1 #0 — Subject + là | Basic sentence: S + là + N |\n| 3 | A1 #4 — Continuous tense | S + đang + V; question forms |\n| 4 | A1 #2 — Past tense | S + đã + V; S + V + rồi |\n| 5 | A1 #6 — Plurals | Những/Các + counter + noun |\n| 6 | A1 #8 — Adjectives | S + Adj; Noun + Adj |\n\n⚠️ **Only 5 of 80 grammar points are in the roadmap**\nThe remaining 75 are in a standalone grammar browser\n(accessible from Practice tab, not gated by progress)","x":-310,"y":10,"width":470,"height":520,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"dialect_notes","type":"text","text":"## Dialect Notes for Teacher\n\n**🔵 Northern vs 🔴 Southern differences taught:**\n\n| Northern | Southern | Meaning | Lesson |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| vâng | dạ | yes (polite) | (in pool, not in lessons) |\n| bố | ba | father | 019 |\n| mẹ | má | mother | 019 |\n| nghìn | ngàn | thousand | 012 |\n| rẽ | quẹo | to turn | 013 (only Southern taught) |\n| — | mắc | expensive (S. only) | 010 |\n| đắt | đắt | expensive (standard) | 008 |\n\n**⚠️ Potential issues:**\n\n1. **`quẹo` without `rẽ`** — Lesson 013 only teaches\n   the Southern form for \"turn\". Northern students\n   won't learn `rẽ` from the roadmap.\n\n2. **`mắc quá` sentence** — The example sentence in\n   lesson 010 is marked Southern-only but will appear\n   for all learners.\n\n3. **`ba` homograph** — `ba` = three (lesson 004) AND\n   `ba` = father-Southern (lesson 019). Could confuse\n   in listen-type exercises.\n\n4. **`bận` / `bán` minimal pair** — busy (023) vs\n   sell (010). Only tone differs. Good teaching\n   opportunity but could frustrate beginners.","x":210,"y":10,"width":470,"height":680,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"vocab_stats","type":"text","text":"## Content Statistics\n\n**Total items in lesson engine:** 96\n• Words: ~75\n• Phrases: ~3\n• Sentences: ~18\n\n**Flashcard library (extra):** 30 words with images\n(some overlap with lesson items)\n\n**Grammar bank:** 80 points (A1: 28, A2: 34, B1: 18)\n\n**Estimated unique vocabulary:** ~120 words\n\n---\n\n**Lesson size (items per lesson):**\n\n| Lesson | Topic | Items |\n|---|---|---|\n| 001 | Hello & Goodbye | 5 |\n| 002 | My Name Is… | 3 |\n| 003 | Please & Sorry | 4 |\n| 004 | Numbers 1–10 | 10 |\n| 005 | I Want… | 6 |\n| 006 | Café Ordering | 5 |\n| 007 | Vietnamese Food | 7 |\n| 008 | How Much? | 6 |\n| 009 | Colors | 10 |\n| 010 | Haggling | 8 |\n| 011 | Fruits & Vegs | 8 |\n| 012 | Big Numbers | 6 |\n| 013 | Directions | 8 |\n| 014 | Taxi & Grab | 7 |\n| 015 | At the Hotel | 6 |\n| 016 | Asking for Help | 7 |\n| 017 | Time & Schedule | 9 |\n| 018 | Weather | 7 |\n| 019 | Family | 10 |\n| 020 | House | 7 |\n| 021 | Hobbies | 7 |\n| 022 | Feelings | 7 |\n| 023 | Invitations | 7 |\n| 024 | At the Party | 7 |","x":730,"y":10,"width":470,"height":810,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"srs_review","type":"text","text":"## Spaced Repetition (Long-term Review)\n\nAfter completing a lesson, all its words enter\nthe SRS review queue.\n\n**Review schedule (if always correct):**\n```\nDay 1:  first review (right after lesson)\nDay 2:  second review (+1 day)\nDay 5:  third review (+3 days)\nDay 12: fourth review (+7 days)\nDay 26: fifth review (+14 days)\nDay 56: sixth review (+30 days)\n```\n\n**If student gets it wrong:** reset to Day 1\n\n**Where reviews happen:**\nBanner on roadmap: \"N words to review\"\nTap → flashcard-style review session\n\n**Two retention loops work together:**\n1. **4 sessions per lesson** = short-term repetition\n   (same words, harder exercises each time)\n2. **SRS flashcards** = long-term retention\n   (individual words on expanding intervals)","x":1250,"y":10,"width":470,"height":520,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"hearts_system","type":"text","text":"## Hearts & Motivation System\n\n**Hearts:** 5 maximum\n• Wrong answer = lose 1 heart\n• 0 hearts = lesson ends (must wait)\n• Regenerate: +1 heart every 30 minutes\n\n**Coins (Đồng ₫):**\n• +10₫ per lesson session completed\n• +25₫ per quiz passed\n\n**Streaks:**\n• +1 per consecutive day of study\n• Reset if a day is skipped\n\n**Node completion:**\n• Lessons: 4 sessions required\n• Quizzes: 1 pass required (immediate)\n• Module quiz: 6 questions\n• Unit quiz: 12 questions","x":1250,"y":580,"width":470,"height":400,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"teacher_suggestions","type":"text","text":"## Suggestions / Things to Review\n\n**1. Content gaps:**\n• Only `tôi` and `bạn` as pronouns in lessons\n  (full pronoun system is in a separate practice module)\n• No classifiers taught in lessons (only in grammar bank)\n• `xanh` ambiguity not addressed\n\n**2. Dialect consistency:**\n• Some lessons mix dialects without clear labeling to student\n• `quẹo` taught without Northern equivalent `rẽ`\n• Consider: should learner choose dialect preference?\n\n**3. Grammar integration:**\n• Only 5 of 80 grammar points in the roadmap\n• Most grammar is optional/self-directed\n• Consider integrating more grammar into lesson path\n\n**4. Sentence coverage:**\n• Only ~18 sentences across 24 lessons\n• Most lessons are word-heavy\n• Consider adding more example sentences per lesson\n\n**5. Data issues:**\n• Grammar point #5 (Pronouns) has empty content (error flag)\n• `ba` = three vs father could confuse in exercises\n\n**6. Item count per lesson varies widely:**\n• Lesson 002 has only 3 items (very short)\n• Lesson 004 and 009 have 10 items (heavy)","x":210,"y":740,"width":470,"height":610,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"grammar_bank","type":"text","text":"## Full Grammar Bank — 80 Points\n\n### A1 Level (28 points)\nBasic sentences · Present/past/future tense · Pronouns\nPlurals · Negation · Adjectives · Adverbs · Prepositions\nQuestion words · Numbers · Counters · Dates · Time\nBecause/But/And · Should · Similarities · Requests\nNot yet · Desire · \"Very\" · Directions · Capacity\n\n### A2 Level (34 points)\nComparisons · Commands · Conditionals · Perception verbs\nQuantifiers · Simultaneous actions · Measurements\nWith/Or/Almost/If · Together · In order to · This/That\nAfter all · Moreover · Until · Must · Used to · Try\nThe more…the more · Suggestions · Intentions\nSurprise · Regret · Hope · Probability · Purpose\nContrast · Advice · Ordering food · Degree adjectives\n\n### B1 Level (18 points)\nNominalization · Passive voice · Quoting · Hearsay\nDegree · Only · Instead · Even though · For now\nSeem to be · Include/Exclude · Certainty · Excessiveness\nInaction · Opinion · Compliments · Emphasis · Approval\n\n⚠️ Grammar point #5 (Pronouns) has a data error —\ncontent is empty in the JSON","x":-310,"y":600,"width":470,"height":760,"color":"6"}
	],
